caption: Fish and chips were tasteless. Coating was soggy and fish no thicker than 1/4-1/2 inch. Darkish color, not haddock. Edible, but didn't  bother finishing.
loaded tots were just okay, onion rings weren't any better. definitely a seafood-focused place but it's popular so I'm sure I'll try again.
Delicious lobster roll. Great fries! They have wine, too!

Harry's waffle fries are nothing short of define. Perfectly crispy. Airy crisp with that oh so tender potato inside. We opted for cheese and bacon to be added on our order and what a reward it was. Glorious melted cheese cascaded over every fry, topped with delicious, thick cut bacon making every bite a delight. Good luck not eating every single bit.  The misses got a BLT and sweet potato fries and again, a perfect example. Awesomely crisp fries. A Diner BLT it's usually a safe bet and Harry's is no exception. 6 perfectly crisp pieces of bacon (that's right, 6 slices of bacon. You know they mean business when they are piling bacon like a boss) stacked with fresh lettuce and ripe tomato slices between two slices of toasted bread made for a very happy woman. She wasn't even hungry before deciding on Harry's but God help you if you tried pulling any of this food away once it hit the table. You'd lose a finger for real.  The country fried steak left something to be desired IMHO. (meaning: it was pretty horrid so if you enjoy good country fried steak, avoid this dish like you're avoiding covid) The saving grace from the steak was a perfect 80's Diner hot fudge sundae. Well presented with a ton of hot fudge had the misses smiling ear to ear. A friendly staff and a cool atmosphere will have us coming back for a second visit
Highly recommend, lots of options. Cash only, but definitely worth it.

This place is great! I have passed this place several times over the years and always wanted to try it. Am glad I finally did.  This is a family owned diner. Staff have always been friendly and welcoming. Makes it real easy to support a local business that appreciates their customers.  Have been several times now and have not been disappointed. Food is fresh and hot. Wide variety of comfort food items. Have tried seafood and sandwiches and all is delicious.  Out of everything I have tried, my favorite so far is their corn chowder. Have hit them up several times during the cold winter and got a steaming bowl of chowder. Always hits the spot!  The quality of the food is excellent. They use fresh ingredients and beat any of the chain restaurants on the strip.  They also serve alcohol if you care to imbibe. Not sure if it is full liquor or just beer and wine.  Also, they are CASH ONLY but they do have an ATM there if you need it.  If you are hungry for some good filling food and friendly staff, stop on by!
